title: For Sale:  1953 Dodge B-4-B
postcontent: 1953 Dodge “Pilot House” B-4-B pickup. As far as I know, she spent her entire life working on a farm in Gainesville, Georgia. In 1978, the farmer who owned her decided to take her apart, perhaps to restore her after 25 years of service. Something must have happened because the farmer never did put her back together and she sat in the barn from 1978 until 2010, when the barn caught fire and burned to the ground. Fortunately, Jolene was saved as she was rolled out of the barn before she herself caught fire. In 2011, a fireman named "Kyle" bought the farm and moved onto the property. Jolene was included and he decided it would be best to find a new home for her. By chance he drove by the Village Garage shop in the East Village of Atlanta and spotted a very similar 1951 Dodge on the property, so he went in to talk to the owner of the shop, "Mike". Mike was into vintage cars and 2 months later, they had Jolene trucked over to his shop.
